  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out or not-applicable (acceptable at MRL 2). One factor (Model inputs) carries an explicitly-flagged wide uncertainty bound on blood viscosity, documented with full rationale and accepted as residual risk given compensating experimental validation.",
