    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-cpb-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels at MRL 2 for a Class II CPB device. Six factors are appropriately scoped out or not applicable with documented rationale consistent with ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. The one explicitly-flagged uncertainty gap — blood viscosity input uncertainty of ±18% — is documented honestly and addressed by a sensitivity analysis confirming that worst-case operating point identification is robust across the full population uncertainty range. The compensating experimental validation (RH index within 95% CI at all 5 operating points) provides sufficient confidence that the model claim is supported. No weakeners are identified. The credibility assessment team accepts the model for the stated COU: identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB conditions.",
